    <text xml:space="preserve">
        
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">
                
                <p>
                    <lb n="1"/>Ik-kāl ceyvit
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>tān koṭumpāḷūṟ
                    <lb n="3"/>kaikkōḷa<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice> maṅka<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice> 
                    <lb n="4"/>tāmatta<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice>-āṉa k<choice><orig>o</orig><reg>u</reg></choice>⌈
                    <lb n="5" break="no"/>lōttuṅka-cōḻa-k
                    <lb n="6" break="no"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> 
                    <lb n="7"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> U
                    <lb n="8" break="no"/>ṭaiyā<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice>
                </p>
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app loc="0">
                        <lem/>
                        <rdg source="bib:SrinivasaRao1979_01"/>
                    </app>
                    
                </listApp>
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                <p n="1-8">
                    He who had this stone<note>That is, the pillar on which the inscription is engraved.</note> made
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">is</supplied>
                    the lord Kulottuṅga <gap reason="lost"/>
                    <hi rend="italic">alias</hi>
                    Maṅkaṉ Tāmattaṉ, a <foreign>kaikkōḷaṉ</foreign><note>A member of the caste of weavers.</note> from Koṭumpālur.
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>For other pillars donated by others <foreign>kaikkōḷaṉ</foreign>s in the same temple see <ref target="DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00018"/> and <ref target="DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00044"/>.</p>
                <p><ref target="DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00044"/> and <ref target="DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00045"/> have been copied as one entry in ARIE 1907-1908. <ref target="DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00044"/> has been later copied as a single entry in ARIE 1968-1969. It seems that we have two pillars, each with an inscription naming its donor.</p>
                <p><bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1968-1969"/></bibl> reads the personal name as <quote>Paṅgan Sāmantan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kolōttuṅgaśōḻak-koṅganāyaṉ alias Ma . Amalan Śēṉaṉ Uḍaiyān</quote>.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Reported in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1907-1908"/></bibl> (ARIE/1907-1908/B/1907/137). See also <bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1968-1969"/></bibl> (ARIE/1968-1969/B/1968-1969/295).</p>
                <p>Edited in <bibl><ptr target="bib:SrinivasaRao1979_01"/></bibl> (<ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv23p0i0137">SII 23.137B</ref>).</p>
                <p>This digital edition by Emmanuel Francis based on <bibl><ptr target="bib:SrinivasaRao1979_01"/></bibl>.</p>
                
